    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nChecked on: `NVIM v0.12.3` and `NVIM v0.13.0-dev`\n\nWhen I yank in Neovim with `vim._core.ui2` enabled in init.lua, the statusline disappears\nand only comes back after I move the cursor.\n\nThis also happens when a plugin prints to the cmdline for example `[osc52] 935 characters copied`.\n\nOn top of that, if I press `enter` while the cmdline is in this disappeared state,\nthe cursor lands inside the message box.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nInitialization : \n```sh\nmkdir ~/.config/tmp  && cd ~/.config/tmp/\nnvim init.lua \n```\n\nConfiguration : \n```lua\nrequire('vim._core.ui2').enable()\nvim.o.cmdheight = 0\n```\n\nSave and exit and launch with : \n\n```sh\nNVIM_APPNAME=tmp nvim README.md\n``` \n\npaste some paragraphs : \n\n```txt\nThe old clock on the wall ticked slower than usual. Rain tapped against the window like impatient fingers.\n\nSomewhere in the distance, a train whistled—low and mournful.\n\nShe turned the page, but the words had already faded into a dream.\n````\n\nDo the following motions : \n\n```\nggVGy\n```\n\noutput in cmdline will blank out the statusline : \n\n```\n\n19 lines yanked\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe expected behaviour is that the statusline must stay visible and on enter the the cursor must not land in message box.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n```bash\nnvim -v NVIM v0.12.3\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1780076327\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n\n```bash\n❯ nvim -v\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1780076327\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI am unsure about whether Vim behaves like that or not.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nAndroid aarch64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nTermux 0.118.3 \n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\necho $TERM                                          xterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\napt install neovim",
