            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The issue persists even on:\n\n```bash\n❯ nvim -v\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1780076327\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n\nInstalled from Termux's official package manager:\n\n```bash\nneovim-nightly/stable,now 0.13.0~dev-740+g635939da3e-0 aarch64 [installed]\n  Ambitious Vim-fork focused on extensibility and agility (nvim-nightly)\n```\n\nMoreover, I have also discovered a new common issue on both versions!\n**Whenever I press enter** after **statusline is disappeared or a new message has arrived in cmdline**,\nmy cursor somehow lands inside the message box (yes that`:message` box).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nMake sure your : \n\n1. **Message separator** is visible (set `:colorscheme default` if message seperator is not visible)\n\n2. **Status line** is **not** disabled. \n\nThen simply reproduce the problem through :\n\n```\nggVGy\nEnter\n```",
